            <title>[LU-10428] LNet events should generated without resource lock held</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10428</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;LNet execute an events with resource lock held, but event handler can allocate an memory, so it will block other callers to lockup over hash table or parallel event execution.&lt;br/&gt;
I will send a patch son.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
